Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Remove the @confit duck legs{2}(1.2 portion) from their packaging and place on a #baking tray{} skin-side up, drizzle with a little oil. Pop on the top shelf of your oven and roast until golden and crispy, ~{25-30%minutes}.

Pour the cold @water{300%ml} for the rice into a medium #saucepan{} with a tight-fitting #lid{}. Stir in the @Jasmine rice{150%g} and @salt{1/4%tsp}, cover with the lid and bring to the boil on medium-high heat. Once boiling, turn the heat down to its lowest setting. Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat (still covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

Trim and thinly slice the @radishes{100%g}. Trim the @carrot{1}. Use a #vegetable peeler{} to peel long ribbons from all sides of the length of the carrot. Stop when you get to the centre. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}). Peel and grate the @ginger{1/2%tbsp}. Cut the @lime{1} into wedges. In a #small bowl{}, mix together the @rice vinegar{15%ml}, @sugar{1%tsp} and a pinch of @salt{}. Add the radishes, mix well and set aside.

Heat a large #frying pan{} over medium heat (no oil). Add the @sesame seeds{7.5%g} and toast until they are lightly golden, ~{1-2%minutes}. Stir frequently.
> TIP: Watch them like a hawk as they can burn easily.

Pop half the sesame seeds into a medium #bowl{} and the other half into a small bowl. Add the @sesame oil{12%ml}, half the ginger and a squeeze of lime juice to the sesame seeds in the medium bowl, season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and mix together. Add the carrot ribbons and mix well to coat then set aside.

Heat a drizzle of oil in the frying pan on medium-high heat. Once hot, add the @mangetout{150%g}, season with salt and pepper and stir-fry until starting to brown, ~{2%minutes}. Add the remaining ginger and garlic and stir-fry for ~{1%minute} more. Remove from the heat and cover to keep warm. Meanwhile, once ready, remove the duck from the oven and use two #forks{} to pull the meat off the bone. Discard the bone.

Pop the @soy sauce{25%ml}, @miso paste{15%g}, @ketjap manis{25%ml} and @honey{15%ml} into a saucepan with the @water{1%tbsp} for the sauce over medium heat. Bring to a simmer and stir until thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}. Add the duck and stir through the sauce. Divide the rice between bowls, top with the duck and its sauce, pickled radishes, sesame carrots and the mangetout. Scatter over the remaining sesame seeds and serve with any remaining lime wedges for squeezing over. Enjoy!